         <property name="text">
          <string># BabbleFish

BabbleFish is a real-time speech translation app. It recognizes speech from a microphone, translates it into the selected language, and produces the result using speech synthesis.

---

# How BabbleFish Works

The speech processing process consists of three sequential stages:

### 1. Speech Recognition

BabbleFish uses the **Whisper** model to convert speech to text.

Before launching, you must select a Whisper model.

* **Small models** are faster and require less video memory (VRAM), but provide less accurate recognition.
* **Large models** significantly improve recognition quality, especially in the presence of noise or accents, but require more VRAM and are slower on low-end graphics cards.

### 2. Text Translation

After recognition, the text is automatically translated into the selected language.

Before launching, specify:

* source language;
* translation language.

### 3. Speech translation

The translated text is converted to speech and played back through the selected output device.

To use speech synthesis, you must first install voice models. This can be done using the **Get more voices...** button.

---

# Using in voice chats

BabbleFish does not automatically create a virtual microphone.

If you want to use translation during calls, streams, or voice recordings, you must install a program that emulates a virtual audio device.

The simplest and most popular option is using [**VB-CABLE**](https://vb-audio.com/Cable/).

## Setup

1. Connect your physical microphone as the **Input Device** in BabbleFish.
2. Select **VB-CABLE Input** as the **Output Device**.
3. In the program where you want to use translation (Discord, Zoom, OBS, games, etc.), select **VB-CABLE Output** as the microphone.

After this, your interlocutors will hear the automatically translated and voiced speech, not your original voice.
</string>
